{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"How many Creationists do we have in the room?"},{"time":3000,"text":"Probably none. I think we're all Darwinians."},{"time":6000,"text":"And yet many Darwinians are anxious, a little uneasy --"},{"time":13000,"text":"would like to see some limits on just how far the Darwinism goes."},{"time":18000,"text":"It's all right."},{"time":20000,"text":"You know spiderwebs? Sure, they are products of evolution."},{"time":24000,"text":"The World Wide Web? Not so sure."},{"time":28000,"text":"Beaver dams, yes. Hoover Dam, no."},{"time":30000,"text":"What do they think it is that prevents the products of human ingenuity"},{"time":36000,"text":"from being themselves, fruits of the tree of life,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and hence, in some sense, obeying evolutionary rules?"},{"time":45000,"text":"And yet people are interestingly resistant"},{"time":49000,"text":"to the idea of applying evolutionary thinking to thinking -- to our thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"And so I'm going to talk a little bit about that,"},{"time":60000,"text":"keeping in mind that we have a lot on the program here."},{"time":64000,"text":"So you're out in the woods, or you're out in the pasture,"},{"time":68000,"text":"and you see this ant crawling up this blade of grass."},{"time":71000,"text":"It climbs up to the top, and it falls,"},{"time":74000,"text":"and it climbs, and it falls, and it climbs --"},{"time":77000,"text":"trying to stay at the very top of the blade of grass."},{"time":81000,"text":"What is this ant doing? What is this in aid of?"},{"time":86000,"text":"What goals is this ant trying to achieve by climbing this blade of grass?"},{"time":93000,"text":"What's in it for the ant?"},{"time":95000,"text":"And the answer is: nothing. There's nothing in it for the ant."},{"time":101000,"text":"Well then, why is it doing this?"},{"time":104000,"text":"Is it just a fluke?"},{"time":106000,"text":"Yeah, it's just a fluke. It's a lancet fluke."},{"time":113000,"text":"It's a little brain worm."},{"time":115000,"text":"It's a parasitic brain worm that has to get into the stomach of a sheep or a cow"},{"time":120000,"text":"in order to continue its life cycle."},{"time":123000,"text":"Salmon swim upstream to get to their spawning grounds,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and lancet flukes commandeer a passing ant,"},{"time":132000,"text":"crawl into its brain, and drive it up a blade of grass like an all-terrain vehicle."},{"time":137000,"text":"So there's nothing in it for the ant."},{"time":141000,"text":"The ant's brain has been hijacked by a parasite that infects the brain,"},{"time":149000,"text":"inducing suicidal behavior."},{"time":153000,"text":"Pretty scary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"Well, does anything like that happen with human beings?"},{"time":160000,"text":"This is all on behalf of a cause other than one's own genetic fitness, of course."},{"time":165000,"text":"Well, it may already have occurred to you"},{"time":170000,"text":"that Islam means \"surrender,\" or \"submission of self-interest to the will of Allah.\""},{"time":180000,"text":"Well, it's ideas -- not worms -- that hijack our brains."},{"time":186000,"text":"Now, am I saying that a sizable minority of the world's population"},{"time":191000,"text":"has had their brain hijacked by parasitic ideas?"},{"time":198000,"text":"No, it's worse than that."},{"time":200000,"text":"Most people have."},{"time":204000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":208000,"text":"There are a lot of ideas to die for."},{"time":210000,"text":"Freedom, if you're from New Hampshire."},{"time":213000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":217000,"text":"Justice. Truth. Communism."},{"time":221000,"text":"Many people have laid down their lives for communism,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and many have laid down their lives for capitalism."},{"time":227000,"text":"And many for Catholicism. And many for Islam."},{"time":231000,"text":"These are just a few of the ideas that are to die for."},{"time":236000,"text":"They're infectious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"Yesterday, Amory Lovins spoke about \"infectious repititis.\""},{"time":243000,"text":"It was a term of abuse, in effect."},{"time":246000,"text":"This is unthinking engineering."},{"time":248000,"text":"Well, most of the cultural spread that goes on"},{"time":252000,"text":"is not brilliant, new, out-of-the-box thinking."},{"time":256000,"text":"It's \"infectious repetitis,\""},{"time":258000,"text":"and we might as well try to have a theory of what's going on when that happens"},{"time":263000,"text":"so that we can understand the conditions of infection."},{"time":269000,"text":"Hosts work hard to spread these ideas to others."},{"time":276000,"text":"I myself am a philosopher, and one of our occupational hazards"},{"time":282000,"text":"is that people ask us what the meaning of life is."},{"time":286000,"text":"And you have to have a bumper sticker,"},{"time":289000,"text":"you know. You have to have a statement."},{"time":292000,"text":"So, this is mine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"The secret of happiness is: Find something more important than you are"},{"time":298000,"text":"and dedicate your life to it."},{"time":300000,"text":"Most of us -- now that the \"Me Decade\" is well in the past --"},{"time":304000,"text":"now we actually do this."},{"time":306000,"text":"One set of ideas or another"},{"time":309000,"text":"have simply replaced our biological imperatives in our own lives."},{"time":313000,"text":"This is what our summum bonum is."},{"time":316000,"text":"It's not maximizing the number of grandchildren we have."},{"time":319000,"text":"Now, this is a profound biological effect."},{"time":323000,"text":"It's the subordination of genetic interest to other interests."},{"time":326000,"text":"And no other species does anything at all like it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"Well, how are we going to think about this?"},{"time":332000,"text":"It is, on the one hand, a biological effect, and a very large one."},{"time":336000,"text":"Unmistakable."},{"time":338000,"text":"Now, what theories do we want to use to look at this?"},{"time":341000,"text":"Well, many theories. But how could something tie them together?"},{"time":344000,"text":"The idea of replicating ideas;"},{"time":347000,"text":"ideas that replicate by passing from brain to brain."},{"time":352000,"text":"Richard Dawkins, whom you'll be hearing later in the day, invented the term \"memes,\""},{"time":357000,"text":"and put forward the first really clear and vivid version of this idea"},{"time":362000,"text":"in his book \"The Selfish Gene.\""},{"time":364000,"text":"Now here am I talking about his idea."},{"time":367000,"text":"Well, you see, it's not his. Yes -- he started it."},{"time":373000,"text":"But it's everybody's idea now."},{"time":376000,"text":"And he's not responsible for what I say about memes."},{"time":380000,"text":"I'm responsible for what I say about memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"Actually, I think we're all responsible"},{"time":388000,"text":"for not just the intended effects of our ideas,"},{"time":394000,"text":"but for their likely misuses."},{"time":398000,"text":"So it is important, I think, to Richard, and to me,"},{"time":402000,"text":"that these ideas not be abused and misused."},{"time":406000,"text":"They're very easy to misuse. That's why they're dangerous."},{"time":409000,"text":"And it's just about a full-time job"},{"time":412000,"text":"trying to prevent people who are scared of these ideas"},{"time":415000,"text":"from caricaturing them and then running off to one dire purpose or another."},{"time":423000,"text":"So we have to keep plugging away,"},{"time":426000,"text":"trying to correct the misapprehensions"},{"time":428000,"text":"so that only the benign and useful variants of our ideas continue to spread."},{"time":436000,"text":"But it is a problem."},{"time":440000,"text":"We don't have much time, and I'm going to go over just a little bit of this and cut out,"},{"time":445000,"text":"because there's a lot of other things that are going to be said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"So let me just point out: memes are like viruses."},{"time":453000,"text":"That's what Richard said, back in '93."},{"time":455000,"text":"And you might think, \"Well, how can that be?"},{"time":457000,"text":"I mean, a virus is -- you know, it's stuff! What's a meme made of?\""},{"time":464000,"text":"Yesterday, Negroponte was talking about viral telecommunications"},{"time":469000,"text":"but -- what's a virus?"},{"time":470000,"text":"A virus is a string of nucleic acid with attitude."},{"time":474000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":475000,"text":"That is, there is something about it"},{"time":477000,"text":"that tends to make it replicate better than the competition does."},{"time":481000,"text":"And that's what a meme is. It's an information packet with attitude."},{"time":485000,"text":"What's a meme made of? What are bits made of, Mom?"},{"time":491000,"text":"Not silicon."},{"time":493000,"text":"They're made of information, and can be carried in any physical medium."},{"time":497000,"text":"What's a word made of?"},{"time":499000,"text":"Sometimes when people say, \"Do memes exist?\""},{"time":504000,"text":"I say, \"Well, do words exist? Are they in your ontology?\""},{"time":508000,"text":"If they are, words are memes that can be pronounced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"Then there's all the other memes that can't be pronounced."},{"time":516000,"text":"There are different species of memes."},{"time":524000,"text":"Remember the Shakers? Gift to be simple?"},{"time":528000,"text":"Simple, beautiful furniture?"},{"time":531000,"text":"And, of course, they're basically extinct now."},{"time":534000,"text":"And one of the reasons is that among the creed of Shaker-dom"},{"time":540000,"text":"is that one should be celibate."},{"time":542000,"text":"Not just the priests. Everybody."},{"time":544000,"text":"Well, it's not so surprising that they've gone extinct. (Laughter)"},{"time":552000,"text":"But in fact that's not why they went extinct."},{"time":557000,"text":"They survived as long as they did"},{"time":560000,"text":"at a time when the social safety nets weren't there."},{"time":562000,"text":"And there were lots of widows and orphans,"},{"time":565000,"text":"people like that, who needed a foster home."},{"time":568000,"text":"And so they had a ready supply of converts."},{"time":571000,"text":"And they could keep it going."},{"time":573000,"text":"And, in principle, it could've gone on forever,"},{"time":575000,"text":"with perfect celibacy on the part of the hosts."},{"time":578000,"text":"The idea being passed on through proselytizing,"},{"time":583000,"text":"instead of through the gene line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"So the ideas can live on in spite of the fact"},{"time":592000,"text":"that they're not being passed on genetically."},{"time":595000,"text":"A meme can flourish in spite of having a negative impact on genetic fitness."},{"time":599000,"text":"After all, the meme for Shaker-dom was essentially a sterilizing parasite."},{"time":608000,"text":"There are other parasites that do this -- which render the host sterile."},{"time":615000,"text":"It's part of their plan."},{"time":617000,"text":"They don't have to have minds to have a plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"I'm just going to draw your attention to just one"},{"time":627000,"text":"of the many implications of the memetic perspective, which I recommend."},{"time":636000,"text":"I've not time to go into more of it."},{"time":638000,"text":"In Jared Diamond's wonderful book, \"Guns, Germs and Steel,\""},{"time":642000,"text":"he talks about how it was germs, more than guns and steel,"},{"time":648000,"text":"that conquered the new hemisphere -- the Western hemisphere --"},{"time":653000,"text":"that conquered the rest of the world."},{"time":655000,"text":"When European explorers and travelers spread out,"},{"time":662000,"text":"they brought with them the germs"},{"time":664000,"text":"that they had become essentially immune to,"},{"time":667000,"text":"that they had learned how to tolerate over"},{"time":670000,"text":"hundreds and hundreds of years, thousands of years,"},{"time":673000,"text":"of living with domesticated animals who were the sources of those pathogens."},{"time":678000,"text":"And they just wiped out -- these pathogens just wiped out the native people,"},{"time":683000,"text":"who had no immunity to them at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"And we're doing it again."},{"time":690000,"text":"We're doing it this time with toxic ideas."},{"time":695000,"text":"Yesterday, a number of people -- Nicholas Negroponte and others --"},{"time":699000,"text":"spoke about all the wonderful things"},{"time":701000,"text":"that are happening when our ideas get spread out,"},{"time":704000,"text":"thanks to all the new technology all over the world."},{"time":706000,"text":"And I agree. It is largely wonderful. Largely wonderful."},{"time":712000,"text":"But among all those ideas that inevitably flow out into the whole world"},{"time":720000,"text":"thanks to our technology, are a lot of toxic ideas."},{"time":725000,"text":"Now, this has been realized for some time."},{"time":728000,"text":"Sayyid Qutb is one of the founding fathers of fanatical Islam,"},{"time":734000,"text":"one of the ideologues that inspired Osama bin Laden."},{"time":739000,"text":"\"One has only to glance at its press films, fashion shows, beauty contests,"},{"time":744000,"text":"ballrooms, wine bars and broadcasting stations.\" Memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"These memes are spreading around the world"},{"time":754000,"text":"and they are wiping out whole cultures."},{"time":759000,"text":"They are wiping out languages."},{"time":761000,"text":"They are wiping out traditions and practices."},{"time":766000,"text":"And it's not our fault, anymore than it's our fault when our germs lay waste"},{"time":774000,"text":"to people that haven't developed the immunity."},{"time":777000,"text":"We have an immunity to all of the junk that lies around the edges of our culture."},{"time":783000,"text":"We're a free society, so we let pornography and all these things -- we shrug them off."},{"time":789000,"text":"They're like a mild cold."},{"time":791000,"text":"They're not a big deal for us."},{"time":793000,"text":"But we should recognize that for many people in the world,"},{"time":797000,"text":"they are a big deal."},{"time":801000,"text":"And we should be very alert to this."},{"time":804000,"text":"As we spread our education and our technology,"},{"time":807000,"text":"one of the things that we are doing is we're the vectors of memes"},{"time":815000,"text":"that are correctly viewed by the hosts of many other memes"},{"time":821000,"text":"as a dire threat to their favorite memes --"},{"time":824000,"text":"the memes that they are prepared to die for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827000,"text":"Well now, how are we going to tell the good memes from the bad memes?"},{"time":831000,"text":"That is not the job of the science of memetics."},{"time":836000,"text":"Memetics is morally neutral. And so it should be."},{"time":842000,"text":"This is not the place for hate and anger."},{"time":846000,"text":"If you've had a friend who's died of AIDS, then you hate HIV."},{"time":851000,"text":"But the way to deal with that is to do science,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and understand how it spreads and why in a morally neutral perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862000,"text":"Get the facts."},{"time":864000,"text":"Work out the implications."},{"time":868000,"text":"There's plenty of room for moral passion once we've got the facts"},{"time":872000,"text":"and can figure out the best thing to do."},{"time":874000,"text":"And, as with germs, the trick is not to try to annihilate them."},{"time":879000,"text":"You will never annihilate the germs."},{"time":882000,"text":"What you can do, however, is foster public health measures and the like"},{"time":888000,"text":"that will encourage the evolution of avirulence."},{"time":894000,"text":"That will encourage the spread of relatively benign mutations"},{"time":901000,"text":"of the most toxic varieties."},{"time":904000,"text":"That's all the time I have,"},{"time":907000,"text":"so thank you very much for your attention."}]}]}